Final Answer

LangChain is an open-source framework that helps developers build LLM-powered applications by connecting language models with external tools, APIs, databases, memory, vector databases, and workflows. It enables features like conversation memory, Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), tool calling, and AI agents.




